Three men were on Saturday rescued in Oko Oba-Agege area of Lagos State after their car sunk in a Lagos canal. In a viral video, a white Accura got trapped in the early hours of Saturday at Oyatoki Canal by Shoretire Street, Oko Oba-Agege, Lagos. Giving update on the incident, Mrs. Margaret Adeseye, Director of the Lagos State Fire and Rescue Service said the car was rescued by the Agege fire crew successfully. She added that all three adults male in the car are presently in safe condition. “The public should be informed that the accura car eventually got trapped by 08:09hrs Saturday at Oyatoki Canal by Shoretire Street, Oko Oba-Agege, Lagos. “However, it was rescued by the Agege Fire Crew of the Lagos State Fire and Rescue Service. “All three adult male occupants are in safe conditions,” the tweet read. …with all three adults male occupants in safe conditions. Mrs. Margaret Adeseye
